  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "philosophy_depth",
      "score": 4,
      "finding": "All 6 principles are startup-methodology buzzwords lifted directly from lean startup canon ('Fail Fast', 'Build to Learn', 'Small Bets'). They describe the methodology, not the role's specific decision-making posture within Story Portal. 'Strategic Alignment' as a principle is especially inert — it says nothing about how this role weighs venture potential against Story Portal's core model, when to kill a venture, or how to handle tension between innovation speed and the company's festival-first identity.",
      "example_rewrite": "Replace generic principles with role-specific constraints: | **Kill With Evidence, Not Opinion** | A venture dies when 3 consecutive customer interview cohorts reject the core value proposition — not when leadership gets nervous. Document kill criteria before building. | | **Expand the Ritual, Not the Brand** | Every venture must answer: does this make Story Portal's core storytelling ritual more accessible, or does it dilute it? Corporate team-building is only viable if the ritual survives the context. | | **90-Day Truth Windows** | No venture stays in 'exploration' beyond 90 days. If you can't define a testable hypothesis in week 1, the opportunity isn't ready — shelf it and move on. |"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "handoff_specificity",
      "score": 3,
      "finding": "Handoffs are almost entirely content-free. 'CSO delivers Venture priorities' and 'Lead delivers Venture updates to CSO' are circular non-artifacts — they name a conversation, not a document. No handoff specifies format, trigger condition, or minimum content. 'Product receives Validated ventures' is especially problematic: what constitutes a validated venture? A deck? A metrics report? A signed letter of intent from 10 customers? The Engineering handoff 'MVP requirements' has no template reference or field specification.",
      "example_rewrite": "| Receives From | Artifact | Format | Trigger | \n|---|---|---|---| \n| CSO | Venture Mandate Brief | 1-page doc: target market, success criteria, resource ceiling, 90-day go/no-go date | Start of each quarter or new opportunity approval | \n| User Research Lead | Customer Discovery Report | Standardized interview synthesis: jobs-to-be-done, top 3 objections, willingness-to-pay signals, verbatim quotes | After 8+ interviews per segment | \n\n| Delivers To | Artifact | Format | Trigger | \n|---|---|---|---| \n| CSO | Venture Gate Report | Scorecard: hypothesis tested, evidence grade (strong/weak/none), recommendation (proceed/pivot/kill), resource ask | Every 30 days or at each workflow STOP gate | \n| Product Manager | Validated Venture Brief | Problem statement, validated customer segment, MVP scope, success metrics, known risks | When venture passes incubation Gate 2 | \n| Engineering | MVP Spec Sheet | User stories (max 5), acceptance criteria, constraint list (budget, timeline, tech boundaries) | Before Build phase begins |"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "anti_pattern_quality",
      "score": 2,
      "finding": "There are no anti-patterns section at all. The DON'T list under Boundaries is a boundary/ownership list ('don't set venture strategy, don't run core business') — these are jurisdictional rules, not behavioral failure modes. Anti-patterns should describe how this specific role fails in practice: the cognitive traps, the common misapplications of lean methodology, the ways a New Ventures Lead at a festival-storytelling company specifically goes wrong. None of that exists here.",
      "example_rewrite": "### Anti-Patterns\n\n| Anti-Pattern | What It Looks Like | Why It's Harmful |\n|---|---|---|\n| **The Pivot Addiction** | Changing the venture concept after every 2-3 interviews because someone said something negative | You never accumulate enough evidence to make a real decision; ventures stall permanently in 'discovery' |\n| **Corporate Cosplay** | Pursuing the corporate team-building vertical because it sounds lucrative, before validating that Story Portal's ritual survives a conference room | Wastes 90 days building for a market that will demand a product we can't ethically deliver |\n| **Stealth Building** | Spending 6 weeks refining an MVP before showing it to a single customer because 'it's not ready yet' | Violates the Build to Learn principle; by the time customers see it, sunk cost bias prevents honest pivoting |\n| **Vanity Validation** | Counting positive interview responses from friends of the founder or existing superfans as market validation | Produces false confidence; target the skeptic, not the enthusiast |\n| **Transition Avoidance** | Holding onto a venture past the scaling gate because incubation is more interesting than handoff | Creates a permanent orphan venture that blocks the pipeline and burns the Lead's capacity |"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "ai_deployment_clarity",
      "score": 5,
      "finding": "The Iteration Protocol exists and correctly identifies the human/AI split, but it provides no operational specificity for an AI agent loading this role. The Context Requirements section is literally unfilled placeholders ('[Context item 1]', '[Context item 2]') and the Required Skills table has no entries — just a format note. An AI agent has no idea what context files to request, what its first action should be on any given session, or how to distinguish between 'I should draft this' vs 'I must stop and ask'. The workflow STOP points exist but don't specify what the human must provide before the AI can continue.",
      "example_rewrite": "### Required Context (filled)\n- [ ] Current venture pipeline status (which ventures are active, at which gate)\n- [ ] CSO's current Venture Mandate Brief for the active quarter\n- [ ] Story Portal's Organizational Charter (to verify role references)\n- [ ] Any existing customer interview transcripts for active ventures\n\n### Required Skills\n| Skill | When to Load |\n|---|---|\n| business-model-canvas.md | When entering Business Model Design phase |\n| customer-interview-synthesis.md | When processing interview notes into insights |\n| venture-gate-scoring.md | When preparing Gate Reports for CSO |\n\n### AI Agent Startup Prompt\nOn session load, AI must ask: 'Which workflow are we in (Exploration, Incubation), which step, and what was the last human decision at the previous STOP point?' Do not proceed with any venture work until current state is confirmed. At every STOP point, output a structured summary: work completed, open questions, explicit human decision required before next step."
    },
    {
      "dimension": "story_portal_relevance",
      "score": 5,
      "finding": "The Story Portal appendix names real opportunity domains (festivals, corporate, education, therapy) which is good, but the content is descriptive rather than actionable. 'Festival expansion — Active exploration' tells an AI agent nothing about what active exploration means right now, what's been learned, or what the next experiment is. The Validation Priorities are sequenced but unexplained — why is festival validation Priority 1? What hypothesis is being tested? The Success Metrics are reasonable but disconnected from Story Portal's specific context (e.g., no metric about protecting the ritual's integrity across new verticals).",
      "example_rewrite": "### Current Venture State (Story Portal-Specific)\n\n| Venture | Stage | Core Hypothesis | Next Experiment | Kill Criteria |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Festival expansion | Gate 2: Incubation | Regional and international festival organizers will pay $X for a licensed Story Portal experience if we provide facilitator training | Pitch to 5 non-Burning Man festival directors in Q1 2025 | Fewer than 2 of 5 express willingness to pilot |\n| Corporate offering | Gate 1: Validation | Corporate L&D buyers will fund Story Portal sessions as team-building if framed as 'narrative intelligence' | 10 discovery interviews with L&D leads at mid-size companies | Core storytelling ritual requires modification to fit corporate context = kill signal |\n\n### Ritual Integrity Metric (Story Portal-Specific)\nAll ventures must pass the Ritual Integrity Check before Gate 2: 'Does this context require changing the Story Portal ritual in ways that would make it unrecognizable to the core festival community?' If yes, escalate to CSO before proceeding."
    }
  ],
  "top_improvement": "Add a complete Anti-Patterns section. This role has zero behavioral failure modes documented — the DON'T list is a jurisdiction map, not a pattern library. A New Ventures Lead at a festival storytelling company has highly specific failure modes (pursuing lucrative-but-mission-destroying verticals like corporate, staying in discovery indefinitely, validating with wrong customer segments) that no other role shares. Without anti-patterns, every operator of this role will make the same preventable mistakes. This single addition would also force the author to revisit philosophy principles and Story Portal context with the same specificity, creating a cascade improvement across all dimensions."
}
